						<summary>

						<p>Uttarāpatīśvara temple, Gaṇapatīśvara shrine, west wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarāja I Year 29.</hi></p>						

						<p>Portions demaged and built in.</p>						

						<p>The record begins with the <hi rend="italic">meykkīrtti, Tirumagaḷ pōla</hi> etc of the king. Records a gift of land to provide for the feeding of devotees (<hi rend="italic">aḍiyār</hi>) at <hi rend="italic">Chiṟuttoṇḍa-ṉambi-māḷigai</hi> at the time of the festival on the day of Tiruvādirai in the month of Chittirai for God Chīrāḷa-dēvar in Tiruchcheṅgāṭṭukkuḍi, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadānam</hi> in Marukal-nāḍu in Mummuḍi-chōḻa-vaḷanāḍu by •• kkai-uḍaiyāṉ Tāyaṉ Śrī-Kṛishṇaṉ. The land gifted was situated in Tirukkaṇṇapuram in the same <hi rend="italic">nāḍu.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">iṟai</hi> on the same was undertaken to be paid by the donor and his descendants <hi rend="italic">(anvayattār)</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">ūrar.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
